.SH SHCrossPowerSpectrumDensityC
Compute the cross\-power spectral density of two complex functions.
.SH Usage
call SHCrossPowerSpectrumDensityC (\f[CR]cilm1\f[R], \f[CR]cilm2\f[R],
\f[CR]lmax\f[R], \f[CR]cspectrum\f[R], \f[CR]exitstatus\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]cilm1\f[R] : input, complex(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmaxin1\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmaxin1\f[R]+1)
The complex spherical harmonics of the first complex function.
.TP
\f[CR]cilm2\f[R] : input, complex(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmaxin2\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmaxin2\f[R]+1)
The complex spherical harmonics of the first complex function.
.TP
\f[CR]lmax\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The maximum spherical harmonic degree of the cross power spectral
